==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ephippium
<hw>E*phip"pi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., saddle
cloth, fr. Gr. <?/; <grk>'epi`</grk> on + <grk>"i`ppos</grk>
horse.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A depression in the
sphenoid bone; the pituitary fossa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>A saddle-shaped cavity to
contain the winter eggs, situated on the back of Cladocera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ephod</ent>⟦br⟧
